21 // From Google gutil
22 #ifndef ARROW_DISALLOW_COPY_AND_ASSIGN
23 #define ARROW_DISALLOW_COPY_AND_ASSIGN(TypeName) \
24  TypeName(const TypeName&) = delete; \
25  void operator=(const TypeName&) = delete
26 #endif

28 #define ARROW_UNUSED(x) (void)x
29 #define ARROW_ARG_UNUSED(x)
30 //
31 // GCC can be told that a certain branch is not likely to be taken (for
32 // instance, a CHECK failure), and use that information in static analysis.
33 // Giving it this information can help it optimize for the common case in
34 // the absence of better information (ie. -fprofile-arcs).
35 //
36 #if defined(__GNUC__)
37 #define ARROW_PREDICT_FALSE(x) (__builtin_expect(x, 0))
38 #define ARROW_PREDICT_TRUE(x) (__builtin_expect(!!(x), 1))
39 #define ARROW_NORETURN __attribute__((noreturn))
40 #define ARROW_PREFETCH(addr) __builtin_prefetch(addr)
41 #elif defined(_MSC_VER)
42 #define ARROW_NORETURN __declspec(noreturn)
43 #define ARROW_PREDICT_FALSE(x) x
44 #define ARROW_PREDICT_TRUE(x) x
45 #define ARROW_PREFETCH(addr)
46 #else
47 #define ARROW_NORETURN
48 #define ARROW_PREDICT_FALSE(x) x
49 #define ARROW_PREDICT_TRUE(x) x
50 #define ARROW_PREFETCH(addr)
51 #endif

54 #define ARROW_MUST_USE_RESULT __attribute__((warn_unused_result))
55 #elif defined(_MSC_VER)
56 #define ARROW_MUST_USE_RESULT
57 #else
58 #define ARROW_MUST_USE_RESULT
59 #endif

76 // clang-format off
77 // [[deprecated]] is only available in C++14, use this for the time being
78 // This macro takes an optional deprecation message
79 #if __cplusplus <= 201103L
80 # ifdef __GNUC__
81 # define ARROW_DEPRECATED(...) __attribute__((deprecated(__VA_ARGS__)))
82 # elif defined(_MSC_VER)
83 # define ARROW_DEPRECATED(...) __declspec(deprecated(__VA_ARGS__))
84 # else
85 # define ARROW_DEPRECATED(...)
86 # endif
87 #else
88 # define ARROW_DEPRECATED(...) [[deprecated(__VA_ARGS__)]]
89 #endif

93 // macros to disable padding
94 // these macros are portable across different compilers and platforms
95 //[https://github.com/google/flatbuffers/blob/master/include/flatbuffers/flatbuffers.h#L1355]
96 #if !defined(MANUALLY_ALIGNED_STRUCT)
97 #if defined(_MSC_VER)
98 #define MANUALLY_ALIGNED_STRUCT(alignment) \
99  __pragma(pack(1)); \
100  struct __declspec(align(alignment))
101 #define STRUCT_END(name, size) \
102  __pragma(pack()); \
103  static_assert(sizeof(name) == size, "compiler breaks packing rules")
104 #elif defined(__GNUC__) || defined(__clang__)
105 #define MANUALLY_ALIGNED_STRUCT(alignment) \
106  _Pragma("pack(1)") struct __attribute__((aligned(alignment)))
107 #define STRUCT_END(name, size) \
108  _Pragma("pack()") static_assert(sizeof(name) == size, "compiler breaks packing rules")
109 #else
110 #error Unknown compiler, please define structure alignment macros
111 #endif
112 #endif // !defined(MANUALLY_ALIGNED_STRUCT)

115 // From googletest
116 // (also in parquet-cpp)
117 
118 // When you need to test the private or protected members of a class,
119 // use the FRIEND_TEST macro to declare your tests as friends of the
120 // class. For example:
121 //
122 // class MyClass {
123 // private:
124 // void MyMethod();
125 // FRIEND_TEST(MyClassTest, MyMethod);
126 // };
127 //
128 // class MyClassTest : public testing::Test {
129 // // ...
130 // };
131 //
132 // TEST_F(MyClassTest, MyMethod) {
133 // // Can call MyClass::MyMethod() here.
134 // }
135 
136 #define FRIEND_TEST(test_case_name, test_name) \
137  friend class test_case_name##_##test_name##_Test
